metadata.name: Antheia
metadata.description:
In Greek mythology, Antheia was one of three goddess known as the Grace. Antheia was also one of the Charites of Aphrodite, and was the goddess of swamps and the goddess of flowers, blossoms, vegetation, and human love. She can be seen in Athenian vase paintings where she was depicted as one of Aphroditeâ€™s attendants.

Antheia carried golden-colored symbols like honey and myrrh to represent her good qualities. She stood for trust, friendship, community, and love.
